We show the effect of image complexity on position error and miss rate for the CG featuring method using synthetic data. Surprisingly, there is a non-monotonic behavior of error with complexity, hitting a maximum for highly striped images that don't vary strongly with depth. However, the featuring miss rate steadily decreases with complexity, reaching only 60% identified particles with our most realistic images
